=E2=80=94=E2=80=94=E2=80=94=E2=80=94=E2=80=94=E2=80=94

CNRS THEMATIC SCHOOL: BDA MDD
		21 - 26 June 2020, Corsica, France=20


The "Distributed Data Masses" (MDD) thematic school is promoted by the =
database research community. It aims to complete the annual French =
national conference "Data Management - Principles, Technologies and =
Applications (BDA)",  whose consistent quality is recognized nationally =
and internationally. The BDA steering committee wished to reinforce the =
pedagogical component (tutorials) within the framework of an independent =
event, a desire which gave birth to the MDD school held in Les Houches =
in 2010, Aussois in 2012, Ol=C3=A9ron in 2014, Urrugne in 2016, and =
finally Aussois 2018. The 2020 edition will take place in Corsica, and =
more precisely at the IGESA center in Bastia (see =
https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=3D9w_zdrTMYKA).=20

The web site and inscriptions will be on-line very soon! Stay tuned, the =
number of attendees is limited. =20

The program for this 6th edition is:

6/21: Sunday afternoon : arrival

6/22: Monday : Ioana Manolescu: Taming Heterogeneous Data, Revisited: =
=46rom Mediators to Modern Polystores with the participation of Rana =
Al-Otaibi, Maxime Buron, Alin Deutsch, Fran=C3=A7ois Goasdou=C3=A9, =
Pawel Guzewicz

6/23: Tuesday : Amr el Abbadi : Blockchain from a distributed and =
database perspective with the participation of Tristan Allard

6/24: Wednesday : Morning : Nicolas Travers : "how to conduct =
experiments", Afternoon : Social event

6/25: Thursday : Angela Bonifati : Augmenting Data Management with AI =
and Machine Learning with the participation of Genoveva Vargas-Solar and =
Jorge Garcia Flores

6/26: Friday : Leaving in the morning.

The target audience of this school consists primarily of young =
researchers in the field of databases as well as in related or =
multidisciplinary fields (management of large amounts of data for =
scientific applications for example). By young researchers, we mean =
doctoral and post-doctoral students. The school is also open to more =
experienced lecturers-researchers and researchers willing to open their =
research interests, the creation of an exchange network or searching for =
continuous training. The school is obviously also open to research =
engineers from the private sector (R&D, startup, etc.). Classes and =
practical sessions are given in english but interactions can also take =
place in french.

